      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773728660806,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 40.65110464268124,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "text": "1] User provides (latitude, longitude, radius) for the nearby search.\n2] Compute the geohash of the user's location using the same precision used to store businesses.\n3] Determine all geohash cells that intersect the search radius \n(typically the center cell plus neighboring cells, or more cells if the radius is larger).\n4] Query the geo index table to retrieve business IDs whose geohash belongs to the candidate cells\n5] Fetch the business records for candidate business IDs, including their latitude and longitude\n6] Compute the exact Haversine distance between the user location and each business location.\n7] Keep only businesses within the requested radius.\n8] Rank and return the results (e.g., by distance, rating, relevance, popularity).\n9] RankScore = 0.35 * distance_score + 0.30 * adjusted_rating_score + 0.20 * popularity_score \n               + 0.10 * relevance_score + 0.05 * open_now_score. Each score is normalized 0 to 1 ",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1] User provides (latitude, longitude, radius) for the nearby search.\n2] Compute the geohash of the user's location using the same precision used to store businesses.\n3] Determine all geohash cells that intersect the search radius \n(typically the center cell plus neighboring cells, or more cells if the radius is larger).\n4] Query the geo index table to retrieve business IDs whose geohash belongs to the candidate cells\n5] Fetch the business records for candidate business IDs, including their latitude and longitude\n6] Compute the exact Haversine distance between the user location and each business location.\n7] Keep only businesses within the requested radius.\n8] Rank and return the results (e.g., by distance, rating, relevance, popularity).\n9] RankScore = 0.35 * distance_score + 0.30 * adjusted_rating_score + 0.20 * popularity_score \n               + 0.10 * relevance_score + 0.05 * open_now_score. Each score is normalized 0 to 1 ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "zEkpDMraa3HDbxS9IYP8M",
